  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Maria Weston Chapman refers contemptuously to the &quot;attempted rehabilitation&quot; of the damaged reputation of Mayor Lyman by his son Theodore Lyman. She also severely criticizes a similar attempt to represent Dr. William Ellery Channing as the head of the anti-slavery movement. Chapman briefly refers to the Boston Public Library.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes envelope with the delivery address: &quot;The Reverend Samuel May, Leicester, Mass&apos;tts.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Enclosed, there is a typed transcript of this manuscript; transcribed by the Boston Public Library.</subfield>
